com.bluegosling.collections.immutable

Class AbstractLinkedImmutableList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • com.bluegosling.collections.immutable.AbstractImmutableList<E>
          • com.bluegosling.collections.immutable.AbstractLinkedImmutableList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of element in the list
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConsList<E>, Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, List<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractLinkedImmutableList.LinkedSubList, LinkedPersistentList

    public abstract class AbstractLinkedImmutableList<E>
extends AbstractImmutableList<E>
implements ConsList<E>
    An abstract base class for immutable list implementations that use linked data structures so that access is sequential. Random access operations in this sort of list have linear runtime complexity. Sub-classes need only implement AbstractCollection.size(), ConsList.first(), and ConsList.rest().
